-- Maria Sharapova Wins French Open First Set Over Italy’s Errani
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2012-06-09T13:52:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-09/maria-sharapova-wins-french-open-first-set-over-italy-s-errani.html
Maria Sharapova  won the first set in
her French Open tennis final against Italy’s Sara Errani as the
Russian tries to win her first title at  Roland Garros  and
complete the career Grand Slam.  Sharapova, the No. 2 seed, took the set 6-3. She got off to
a quick start, leading No. 21 Errani 3-0 after the first 8
minutes of the match. Errani got it to 4-2. Sharapova held at
love, and had two set points, but couldn’t win them. She served
out the set.  The Russian has lost just 1 set so far in the Paris
tournament.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  